sections.content: The property covered under Gift Settlement Deed No. 415 of 2026, dated 30/Jan/2026, executed by 1. Vuggina Satyanarayana 2. Vuggina Rambabu, in favour of Vuggina Satyanarayana, (Where as Donee is the represented himself 1st Donor, Son to the 2nd Donor), towards the property admeasuring an extent of 210 Sq. Yds, bearing house number 2-146, Assessment number 269, comprised in survey number 127, situated in Govindapuram Village and Grama Panchayath, Jaggampeta Mandal, erstwhile East Godavari, now within the District of Kakinada, registered at sub-registrar office Jaggampeta, is bounded as follows: North by: 32 Ft 6 Inches Pathway South by: 32 Ft 6 inches Site of Uggina Chantibabu East by: 58 Ft House of Uggina Narayudu West by: 58 Ft Site of Donors
It is noted from the given documents and EC that the schedule property is not part of any active Mortgage or Lease Deed.

Note: It should be noted that the deed is executed by Donor representing himself as the Donee, thereby acting in a dual capacity, which constitutes a conflict of interest and is legally invalid. Therefore, it is advisable for the F.I. to verify the same and proceed as per its internal policy. Further, It is to be noted that the online EC has been verified using the key parameters, namely the Document Number, Survey Number/House Number, and Split Survey/House Number of the concerned SRO, as per the Deed. However, cross-verification across multiple SROs has not been carried out due to the AP portal’s requirement of separate passwords for each search parameter, and the OTP-based authentication mechanism makes searches across multiple SROs operationally infeasible.
